bio.experienceSummary: As a caregiver, I'm driven by my passion for fostering children's growth and development. With five years of experience, I've discovered that being patient, calm, creative, and approachable helps me connect with children. I keep parents informed about their child's day through daily reports or regular updates. When it comes to household rules, I can confidently enforce them. From outdoor sports to board games and educational activities, I enjoy a variety of games. With my background in Early Childhood Education and coursework in Early Child Development, complemented by First Aid and CPR Training, I'm well-equipped to ensure a safe and nurturing environment for your child. Whether it's cooking meals, carpooling, light housekeeping, traveling, or supervising swimming, I'm happy to assist. Let's work together to create a positive and enriching experience for your child and family.

Hi, I'm Katty!

I have several years of experience working with children, primarily in early childhood education. I was a teacher assistant at Seven Oaks Academy Preschool, working with ages 0-8, mainly Pre-K and 3-year-olds. In high school, I took early childhood education courses and received CPR, First Aid, and AED training.

Beyond formal experience, I've provided childcare for families, caring for children ages 2-7, and I volunteer as a children's teacher at my church. I'm patient, caring, and adventurous, and I love engaging kids in learning and exploration.

I'm looking for a job that offers trust, respect, flexibility, and communication. I'm a recent KSU graduate in finance and accounting, finishing up an internship while seeking full-time work. In my free time, I enjoy hiking, baking, traveling, and reading.

My skills include attentiveness, engagement, and responsibility.

Let's connect!

I recently worked with two families. One for two years, starting when the children were 3 months old and 2 years old. The other family had 2 children, ages 1 and 4. I have also been a nanny for other families with multiple children from newborn to 8 years old. I am comfortable with light housekeeping such as laundry, dishes, and tidying up. I love interacting with children and engaging them in learning activities. I don't use my phone while working. I work best with kind and understanding families. I have my Childcare Professional Credentials. I am also certified in First Aid and CPR. I am a mother and grandmother to 3 grandchildren who are my pride and joy. I am a very compassionate, honest, hardworking, dependable individual. I love animals. I am a non-smoker. I also am Covid Vaccinated.

description.displayText: We cannot recommend Rebecca enough. Her love for children, professionalism, communication skills, proactive nature, and positive impact on our children's lives make her an exceptional nanny. If you are looking for someone who will not only care for your children but also nurture their development and create a loving environment, Rebecca is the perfect choice. She has become an invaluable part of our family, and we are grateful for her dedication.

bio.experienceSummary:
As a childcare provider, I'm passionate about fostering children's growth and development. With three years of experience, I strive to create a safe, nurturing environment where children can thrive. My patient and calm nature allows me to handle challenging situations with ease, while my creativity and imagination ensure that learning is always fun and engaging.

I believe in open communication with parents and provide regular updates on their child's day, both verbally and in writing. I'm also very comfortable enforcing household rules and ensuring children understand the importance of discipline.

I enjoy playing a variety of games with children, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational games that promote learning. My skills and training include First Aid and CPR certification, as well as coursework in early child development.

I'm willing to help with cooking, meal preparation, carpooling, light housekeeping, and swimming supervision.

I am a dedicated and experienced caregiver with a strong background in childcare, household management, and educational support. With years of hands-on experience working with infants, toddlers, school-age children, teenagers, as well as children with special needs, including those who are autistic and disabled, I provide a nurturing and engaging environment tailored to each child's needs. I'm passionate about providing high-quality childcare and household support, ensuring families have a safe, structured, and loving environment. With a strong ability to multitask, communicate effectively, and create meaningful connections with children, including those with special needs, and pets alike, I am a dependable and compassionate caregiver.

description.originalText: Ms.J nannied my toddler and my needs son that was originally nonverbal. She is so hands-on and very interactive educational support and development promoting my son to say small words. She also had my toddler well potty trained right before her birthday

bio.experienceSummary: Hello everyone! I'm Elisabeth and I'm 24 years old. I am a graduate of the University of Georgia and am looking for babysitting and tutoring opportunities before I start rotations for medical school. I have been babysitting for outside families since I was 13, but I have been babysitting my twin younger siblings since I was 12. I have experience with children from ages newborn to age 15. Back in Athens, I worked at the YMCA as a child watch worker and dance/cheer coach. I also taught 6th, 7th and 8th graders in Columbus, GA at Baker Middle School, in addition to subbing at a variety of elementary, middle and high schools; I have plenty of experience with children! I love playing games and helping children with their homework. Creativity is my forte, and I always think of fun and educational ways to keep children entertained! I also love dogs, and I'm very comfortable around them. I'm also available to do light cleaning as well and look forward to interacting with you guys!

Over the years, I've gained extensive experience caring for and tutoring children through babysitting, tutoring sessions, and working at summer camps since middle school. I truly enjoy working with children and find fulfillment in helping them learn and grow.

I'm known for being responsible, trustworthy, and reliable, and I pride myself on creating a fun, energetic environment for the kids I work with. Whether it's assisting with homework or planning fun activities, I'm committed to providing both care and a positive experience.

I'm excited to connect with families in need of a dedicated caregiver and look forward to the opportunity to support your child's well-being and development.
